ms", "2026-03-08", "50-64", "1", "0", "0", "A/H1N1", "Y"], ["Adams", "2026-03-05", "65+", "1", "0", "0", "A/H3N2", "N"], ["Adams", "2026-03-07", "65+", "1", "0", "0", "A/H3N2", "Y"], ["Jackson", "2026-03-08", "0-4", "1", "0", "0", "A/H3N2", "Y"], ["Jackson", "2026-03-07", "5-17", "1", "1", "0", "A/H3N2", "Y"], ["Jackson", "2026-03-08", "18-49", "1", "0", "0", "A/H3N2", "Y"], ["Jackson", "2026-03-05", "18-49", "1", "0", "0", "A/H3N2", "Y"], ["Jackson", "2026-03-07", "65+", "1", "0", "0", "B/Victoria", "N"]]}}, "goldenOutput": {"influenza_surveillance_week10_2026.docx": {"type": "docx", "content": [{"kind": "h1", "text": "State of Columbia"}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "Department of Health"}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "Influenza Surveillance Report"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "MMWR Week 10 | March 2–8, 2026"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Report prepared: March 12, 2026"}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "1. Executive Summary"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Influenza activity in the State of Columbia during MMWR Week 10 (March 2–8, 2026) is classified as MODERATE. A total of 211 cases were reported statewide, with 16 hospitalizations and 1 deaths. Activity is increasing compared to the previous week."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Notable findings: Jefferson and Madison counties report the highest incidence rates. The 5-17 age group is the most affected. A/H3N2 remains the dominant circulating strain, accounting for 51% of typed specimens."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "2. Surveillance Data Summary"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "During Week 10, Columbia reported 211 influenza cases across 8 counties. Of these, 156 (73.9%) were laboratory-confirmed. There were 16 hospitalizations and 1 deaths attributed to influenza."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "3. Geographic Distribution"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "The table below presents influenza cases, hospitalizations, and incidence rates by county for Week 10."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Hotspot counties: Jefferson (21.8 per 100k) and Madison (16.6 per 100k) have the highest incidence rates and warrant targeted surveillance."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "4. Age Distribution Analysis"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "The 5-17 age group shows the highest incidence rate at 26.8 per 100,000. Children aged 5–17 also show elevated rates consistent with school-based transmission. Adults 65+ have the highest hospitalization rate, reflecting greater disease severity in older populations."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "5. Strain Distribution"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "A/H3N2 continues to be the dominant circulating strain this season, accounting for 51% of all typed specimens. This is consistent with regional and national surveillance data indicating A/H3N2 predominance during the 2025–26 season."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "6. Trend Analysis"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "The following table summarizes statewide influenza activity over the past four weeks."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Influenza activity has been increasing over the reporting period. Total cases increased by approximately 62% from Week 7 to Week 10, indicating a sustained upward trajectory. This trend is consistent with the typical late-season acceleration observed in late winter / early spring."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "7. Hospitalization & Mortality"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "The overall hospitalization rate for Week 10 is 7.6% (16 of 211 cases). The case-fatality rate (CFR) is 0.47% (1 deaths among 211 cases). Among hospitalized patients, the in-hospital fatality rate is 6.2%."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Adults aged 65 and older and children aged 0–4 remain the highest-risk groups for severe outcomes. Targeted clinical guidance for early antiviral treatment in these populations is warranted."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "8. Recommendations"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "1. Vaccination outreach: Intensify messaging in high-incidence counties (Jefferson, Madison) emphasizing that influenza vaccination remains the most effective prevention measure. Target unvaccinated individuals in the 65+ and 0–4 age groups."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "2. Antiviral treatment: Remind healthcare providers to prescribe oseltamivir or baloxavir promptly for patients in high-risk groups presenting within 48 hours of symptom onset."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "3. Infection control: Reinforce respiratory hygiene and hand-washing guidance in schools and long-term care facilities. Consider enhanced visitor screening in facilities with active outbreaks."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "4. Surveillance enhancements: Increase sentinel provider reporting in Jefferson and Madison counties. Expand genomic sequencing of circulating strains to monitor for antigenic drift."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "5. Public communication: Issue a public advisory noting elevated influenza activity and encouraging symptomatic individuals to stay home, seek testing, and contact their healthcare provider."}, {"kind": "h2", "text": "9. Methodology Notes"}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Data sources: Case data are reported by county health departments through the Columbia Electronic Disease Surveillance System (CEDSS). Demographic estimates are based on the 2025 Columbia State Census Bureau population estimates."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Rate calculations: Incidence rates are calculated as (case count / population) × 100,000. Age-specific rates use the corresponding age-group population denominators. Case-fatality rate (CFR) is calculated as (deaths / total cases) × 100."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Limitations: Case counts may underestimate true incidence due to underreporting and limited testing. Prior-week summary rows represent aggregated county-level data and are not stratified by age group. Lab-confirmed status may lag due to specimen transport times."}, {"kind": "p", "text": "Report prepared by the Columbia State Epidemiology Unit. For questions, contact: epi@health.columbia.gov."}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["Metric", "Count"], ["Total reported cases", "211"], ["Laboratory-confirmed cases", "156"], ["Hospitalizations", "16"], ["Deaths", "1"], ["Statewide incidence (per 100k)", "16.4"]]}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["County", "Cases", "Hospitalizations", "Deaths", "Rate per 100k"], ["Jefferson", "60", "7", "1", "21.8"], ["Madison", "24", "1", "0", "16.6"], ["Franklin", "56", "3", "0", "16.0"], ["Hamilton", "15", "1", "0", "15.8"], ["Adams", "11", "0", "0", "15.3"], ["Lincoln", "26", "3", "0", "14.4"], ["Monroe", "14", "0", "0", "11.7"], ["Jackson", "5", "1", "0", "10.4"], ["TOTAL", "211", "16", "1", "16.4"]]}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["Age Group", "Cases", "Hospitalizations", "Deaths", "Rate per 100k"], ["5-17", "55", "3", "0", "26.8"], ["0-4", "14", "3", "0", "18.2"], ["65+", "40", "6", "1", "17.3"], ["18-49", "70", "1", "0", "13.6"], ["50-64", "32", "3", "0", "12.5"]]}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["Strain / Subtype", "Cases", "Proportion"], ["A/H1N1", "55", "26.1%"], ["A/H3N2", "108", "51.2%"], ["B/Victoria", "48", "22.7%"], ["Total", "211", "100.0%"]]}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["Week", "Total Cases", "Hospitalizations", "Deaths"], ["Week 7", "130", "6", "0"], ["Week 8", "159", "5", "0"], ["Week 9", "189", "24", "1"], ["Week 10 (current)", "211", "16", "1"]]}, {"kind": "table", "rows": [["High-Risk Group", "Cases", "Hospitalization Rate", "CFR"], ["0-4", "14", "21.4%", "0.00%"], ["65+", "40", "15.0%", "2.50%"], ["50-64", "32", "9.4%", "0.00%"]]}]}}}